cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques applied to clinical datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of word embeddings, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the encoding of domain knowledge, which is a common theme in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) research. The paper also discusses the correlation of the word vectors with clinical experts, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
